1. Introduction

Welcome to WeCollect, a smart waste collection app developed by Clenville. We are committed to safeguarding your privacy and ensuring transparency regarding how we handle your personal information. This Privacy Policy outlines how WeCollect collects, uses, and protects user data, providing insights into our practices and your rights.

2. Information We Collect

WeCollect may collect the following information from users to enhance their experience:

Personal Information: Name, email address, phone number, and location data.
Usage Data: Information on how you interact with the app, including features used, times of access, and frequency of visits.
Device Information: Details about the device used to access WeCollect, such as device ID, operating system, and IP address.
Location Data: To connect you with nearby collection points, WeCollect may collect real-time location data, with your consent.
3. How We Use Your Information

WeCollect uses your information to:

Enable app features, such as connecting you to nearby collection points.
Provide rewards based on the volume of waste you recycle.
Track and display your environmental impact over time.
Improve our services through usage analysis and feedback.
Communicate important updates, rewards, and other relevant notifications.
4. Data Sharing and Disclosure

We do not sell your personal information. However, we may share your data with:

Recycling Partners: Authorized recycling facilities to facilitate the waste collection process.
Service Providers: Trusted third parties who assist in app functionality and analytics.
Legal Requirements: We may disclose information as required by law to comply with legal obligations or protect the safety of our users.
5. Data Security

We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your data against unauthorized access, alteration, or destruction. However, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure, so we cannot guarantee absolute security.

6. User Rights

Depending on your location, you may have rights under privacy laws, such as:

Access: Request a copy of the personal data we hold about you.
Correction: Update or correct any inaccuracies in your data.
Deletion: Request the deletion of your personal data, subject to certain exceptions.
Objection and Restriction: Request limited use of your data in specific circumstances.
7. Data Retention

We retain personal data as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy, or as required by law.

8. Third-Party Links

WeCollect may contain links to third-party websites or services. We are not responsible for the privacy practices of these third parties. We recommend reviewing the privacy policies of these services before providing any personal information.

9. Changes to This Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy to reflect changes in our practices or for legal or operational reasons. Users will be notified of any significant changes via the app.

10. Contact Us

For questions or concerns about our Privacy Policy or your data, please contact us at:
info@clenville.com
